  "text": "For antibody production, rabbits were injected subcutaneously with 200 [~g of purified Cdc48p in complete Freund's adjuvant emulsion and boosted after 3 and 6 weeks with 100 pg of Cdc48p in incomplete Freund's adjuvant. Serum was collected starting 2 weeks after the last injection. IgG was purified from rabbit serum on HiTrap protein G columns (Pharmacia) as described by the manufacturer. Antiserum was affinity purified on nitrocellulose blots according to the protocol of [CITATION_1] , using 5 p,g of purified Cdc48p as the affinity adsorbent.",
